title: Orbán to visit White House to try to broker Trump-Putin summit for peace in Ukraine
summary: Hungary's Prime Minister is negotiating for an exemption from US sanctions on Russian oil, following frustrations expressed by former President Trump regarding Kremlin policies. This move highlights Hungary's ongoing reliance on Russian energy supplies. The discussions reflect broader tensions in US-Hungary relations amid the geopolitical landscape.

title: Pluribus review – the audacity of the Breaking Bad creator’s new TV show is incredible
summary: In a bold television venture, Rhea Seehorn stars as the only U.S. citizen unaffected by an alien virus that brings overwhelming happiness to the rest of the world. The show blends bleak themes with dark comedy, highlighting the stark contrast of her character's reality. Overall, it's a unique take on joy and isolation in a surreal setting.

title: ‘If there’s a free alternative, I’ll eat healthily’: how Sweden devised brilliant school meals
summary: A pilot program provides students with nutritious breakfasts made from donated surplus food, promoting health and sustainability. This initiative is rooted in the ‘folkhem’ welfare model, emphasizing community support and well-being. The scheme aims to address food waste while improving students' nutrition and overall health.

title: ‘Long on talk and short on action’: Papua New Guinea leader criticises Cop climate summits ahead of Brazil meeting
summary: James Marape, the Prime Minister of Papua New Guinea, previously boycotted a meeting in protest but has decided to attend Cop30 this year. His participation is motivated by "encouraging signs" regarding climate finance. This indicates a potential shift in his stance on international climate discussions.
